BEGIN_DESC
A Shuttle-A class transport vessel is ready for take-off from Habana International Spaceport.

This vessel class is primarily used for orbital operations and low-gravity low-atmosphere planet descents.
Launching it from Earth can be a challenge.

To take off, you need the auxiliary pods in hover configuration
in addition to the standard hover thrusters.

Once free of the pad, set a climb angle of 60 deg. and adjust hovers to maintain zero angle of attack.

As you leave the lower atmosphere and gather speed, reduce your climb angle and slowly reduce hover
thrust.

You should just about be able to make LEO before running out of fuel.
END_DESC

